 {"id":"beads_rust-c0v","title":"EPIC: Agent Ergonomics & Dual-Mode CLI","description":"# Agent Ergonomics & Dual-Mode CLI

## Background & Rationale

Based on research of mature CLI tools (beads_viewer, cass, xf) and 2025-2026 best practices for AI coding agent integration, br needs a dual-mode CLI architecture that serves both human developers (interactive mode) and AI coding agents (structured output mode).

### Why This Matters
- ~85% of developers now use AI tools for coding (2025 data)
- AI agents like Claude Code need deterministic, structured JSON output
- Same binary should serve both humans and agents - single source of truth
- Current br outputs are human-friendly but not agent-optimized

## Goals
Implement `--robot-*` flags and structured output modes that enable AI coding agents to programmatically interact with br, parse results, and make intelligent decisions based on issue data.

## In-Scope
- `--robot-help` - Machine-readable help (JSON schema of commands/flags)
- `--robot-triage` - Ranked actionable items with scores and reasons
- `--robot-next` - Single top priority item with claim command
- `--robot-plan` - Execution tracks showing parallelizable work
- `--robot-graph` - Dependency DAG as JSON/DOT/Mermaid
- `--robot-priority` - Priority misalignment detection
- Structured JSON error output with codes, hints, retryable flags
- TTY detection for automatic mode switching
- `NO_COLOR` environment variable support

## Out-of-Scope (v1)
- Full TUI mode (separate epic)
- MCP server integration (separate epic)

## Acceptance Criteria
- All `--robot-*` flags implemented and documented
- JSON output is deterministic and stable across runs
- Error output includes structured metadata
- Agent workflows (ready → claim → work → close) are streamlined
- Documentation includes agent integration guide

## Technical Approach

### Structured Error Output
```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "ISSUE_NOT_FOUND",
    "message": "Issue bd-xyz123 not found",
    "hint": "Did you mean bd-xyz12? Use 'br list' to see all issues",
    "retryable": false
  }
}
```

### Robot Mode Detection
- Explicit `--robot-*` flags take precedence
- `--json` implies structured output
- Check `isatty(stdout)` for auto-detection
- Respect `NO_COLOR` and `TERM=dumb`

## References
- Anthropic: Claude Code Best Practices for Agentic Coding
- beads_viewer: `--robot-triage`, `--robot-plan` implementation
- cass: `--robot-help` pattern
- Charm ecosystem: gum, lipgloss for styling

